ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Study phase at the index visit
Length of stay in minutes
90th percentile of LOS (Length of stay) in TAU (Treatment As Usual) phase by site

ED triage time
Does the chief complaint involve psychiatric behavior?
Is suicidal thoughts and/or behavior noted as part of the presenting complaint?
Notes: 0= No/Not documented; 1= Suicidal ideation alone (no behavior); 2= Suicidal behavior (including prep, aborted, interrupted, and actual attempts); 3= Unsure

ElementDescription: Was any documentation completed in the Patient Safety Screener (PSS-3), including 'Refused' or 'Patient unable to complete'?
Based on the Patient Safety Screener (PSS3), did the patient screen positive for suicide risk?
On the initial Patient Safety Screener (PSS3), did the patient report: Over the past 2 weeks, they had thoughts of killing themselves?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes; 2= Refused; 3= Patient unable to complete; 99= Not documented

ElementDescription: On the initial Patient Safety Screener (PSS3) did the patient report: Having ever attempted to kill themselves?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes; 2= Refused; 3= Patient unable to complete; 99= Not documented

ElementDescription: When did suicide attempt last happen?
Notes: 1= Within the past 24 hours (including today); 3= Between 24hrs and 6 months ago; 4= More than 6 months ago; 5= Refused; 99= Not documented

ElementDescription: Placeholder hospital ID assigned to each ED location
Did patient's initial risk level from Patient Safety Screener (PSS3) change during course of this visit in the [ed_location_id] ED?
What is patient's final risk level on Patient Safety Screener (PSS3)/Orders?
Notes: 1= Mild; 2= Moderate; 3= High; 4= Negligible; 99= Not Documented

ElementDescription: Was the patient evaluated by a mental health professional during this visit in the [ed_location_id] ED?  (including EMH evals, social work evals, BHS assessments)
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes; 2= Refused; 3= Patient unable to complete; 4= Offered but unable to complete due to time or staffing; 99= Not documented

ElementDescription: Is the Emergency Mental Health Evaluation in the patient's record?
Was the evaluation completed by telehealth?
Was a written safety plan created for the patient while in the [ed_location_id] ED?
Notes: 0= No (No documentation of a written safety plan being created for the patient); 1= Partial (Documentation of a written safety plan being created in text but no safety plan was located in the chart); 2= Complete (A copy of the written safety plan found in patient's chart)

What type of behavioral health follow-up was arranged for the patient? (Note: ED-SAFE follow-up calls do not count)
Notes: 1= The team scheduled a new BH appointment for the patient at a specific date and time; 2= The patient already had a scheduled BH appointment coming up; 3= The patient was given the name of a new specific BH provider and told to follow up with them; 4= The patient was told to follow up with their existing BH provider; 5= There was a vague reference to BH referral, for example patient was given a list of providers; 6= Patient was offered help arranging a follow-up appointment but declined; 99= Unknown

ElementDescription: Was the patient randomized to ED-SAFE Follow-up? (Yes if the patient's year of birth is an even number else, No if it is odd)
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes; 88= N/a (TAU, Control Site, or ED-SAFE not started yet)

ElementDescription: Was there any documentation that intentional self-harm was attempted or occurred during the [ed_location_id] ED visit?
Notes: 0= No/Not documented; 1= Yes, intentional self-injury without apparent intent to die; 2= Yes, intentional self-injury with at least some intent to die; 3= Intent Unsure

ElementDescription: Please rate the outcome of the intentional self-injury while in the [ed_location_id] ED
Notes: 1= No harm; 2= Mild injury but no treatment required example superficial laceration, abrasion; 3= Mild/moderate injury requiring medical attention but no increased length of stay or requiring hospital admission example suturing for laceration, tests for retained foreign body; 4= Severe injury requiring hospitalization or increased length of stay example patient taken to OR for surgery/intervention; 5= Death

ElementDescription: Location of ED Disposition
Notes: 1= Home; 2= Home with CHL follow-up; 3= Transferred to EMH; 4= Admitted to medical ward/observation; 5= Admitted/transferred to psychiatric ward/facility; 6= Admitted to substance abuse treatment facility; 7= Left against medical advice; 8= Left without being seen; 9= Transferred to University ED; 88= Other; 99= Not documented

ElementDescription: Please select patient disposition following EMH transfer
Notes: 1= Home; 2= Admitted to medical ward/observation; 3= Admitted/transferred to psychiatric ward/facility; 4= Admitted to substance abuse treatment facility; 5= Left against medical advice; 88= Other; 99= Not documented
